{"id":"tn-7tk","title":"Daemon handoff breaks with pre-IPC daemons after legacy type removal","description":"After removing DaemonRequest/DaemonResponse (tn-6db), client.rs always sends IpcMessage::Request for pings. An old daemon that only speaks the legacy protocol will fail the ping, causing ensure_daemon() to classify it as absent, delete its socket, and start a second daemon — stranding the old process and dropping sessions.

The ensure path should handle unknown/failed ping responses more gracefully: detect that *something* is listening on the socket (connect succeeded) but doesn't speak the current protocol, and attempt graceful shutdown before replacing.

Low urgency since there's no deployed daemon fleet, but the failure mode is destructive (session loss).","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"marcinek.matthew@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-04-05T06:15:50Z","created_by":"GGPrompts","updated_at":"2026-04-05T06:15:50Z","labels":["daemon","ready"]}

